- Label the complete project method as `µ£¼µ¢ćµ¢╣µ│Ģ` in Chinese-facing main-result and SOTA-comparison legends, captions, plot data, and manifest metadata, and translate it to `Proposed method` only when converting to an English manuscript. Label external comparison methods by source only, for example `Pappu2017` or `AuthorYear`, and record the corresponding paper or reference in the caption, manifest, or evidence map.
- Keep external SOTA/baseline comparisons and proposed-method ablations in separate figure groups unless the manuscript explicitly needs a combined view. SOTA/baseline comparisons may cover primary metrics, secondary metrics, cross-case generalization, runtime, or other performance views.
